Interface OperatorSelecter<O extends Operator<?>>

Type Parameters:
O - type of Operator
All Superinterfaces:
EvolutionObject
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractOperatorSelecter, CrossoverOperatorSelecterImpl, MutateOperatorSelecterImpl, NEATCrossoverOperatorSelecterImpl, NEATMutateOperatorSelecterImpl
public interface OperatorSelecter<O extends Operator<?>>
extends EvolutionObject

The OperatorSelecter describes the methods for a collection of Operators that are retrieved probabilistically, without replacement. It includes a reset() method to return the OperatorSelecter to it full state.

Author:
Luis Guimbarda
